snippet: As much of Cairo exploded in euphoria, parts of the city fell silent where President Mohamed Morsi’s loyalists protested to stave off what they saw as a threat to democracy.
abstract: Much of Cairo explodes in euphoria over ouster of Pres Mohamed Morsi, but parts of city that are home to his Islamist supporters fall silent, with Morsi loyalists confused and fearful about what happens next.
lead_paragraph: As much of Cairo exploded in euphoria, parts of the city fell silent where President Mohamed Morsi’s loyalists protested to stave off what they saw as a threat to democracy.

headline.main: For Egypt’s Islamists, Confusion and Fear Amid Celebration
